    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Blocked by #2161\n\n### Problem\n\nThere is no way for different remote clients to have different color schemes.\n\nRelated #40175 \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAllow remote clients to set (different) color schemes at will.\n\n***Obvious disclaimer***: This is a massive refactor and probably out of scope for now (making colorschemes non-global would be complex and a big divergence from upstream) but I wanted to canonicalize it here.\n\nI can imagine this not being done for _a while_ but I still think this is a reasonable feature to expect from NeoVim in the (very) long run. ",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
