        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Ah. So this is blocked by the actual multihead design.\n\n1. (nit) I'd mark this as medium complexity: the actual changes associated with this request are not bad (adding a channel id to `TermResponse` and rendering accordingly - I actually already did it on my fork). Instead, all the multihead abstractions, AFAIK, are what make this challenging.\n2. Is there any way to pursue this orthogonally to multihead design? I can only imagine a pipeline for \"per-ui\" options. This is probably thinking too far ahead before multi-head is further fleshed out.\n3. Following the above, how can we mark this as sort of \"internally blocked\" by multihead (do we have a github setting for it)? I just updated the main issue.",
